LOGIN: Connect to Discord with the token %1
LOGIN_TOOLTIP: Connect your bot to Discord. To get your bot token, go to https://discord.com/developers/ and create an application. Make it a bot and copy the token
ON_MESSAGE: When the bot receives a message
ON_MESSAGE_TOOLTIP: Emitted when the bot receives a message
ON_CONNECTED_TOOLTIP: Event emitted when your bot is connected to Discord.
NAME: Name
RES_ADD_REACTION_MISSING_REACTION: A valid emoji must be provided.
ADD_REACTION: Add a reaction %1 to the message
TITLE: Title
CHECK_PERMISSIONS: Check the permissions of the members
MEMBER_HAS_PERMISSION: If the member %1 has the permission %2
ON_MEMBER_JOIN: When a member joins a server

RES_MISSING_CONTENT: You must specify a valid content to reply!

RES_BAN_MEMBER_MISSING_MEMBER: You must specify a valid member to be banned!

GET_CHANNEL: Get the channel with %2 equal to %1

RES_SET_SERVER_NAME_NEW_NAME: You must specify a new valid name for the server!
SET_SERVER_NAME: Change name of server %1 new name %2
RES_GET_ROLE_VALUE: You must specify a valid name or role ID!
RES_GET_SERVER_VALUE: You must specify a valid server name or ID!
GET_MEMBER: Get member with %2 equal to %1 on server %3
INIT_TOOLTIP: Allows you to use Discord blocks!
JOINING_GUILD_RAW: %1 of the server of the joining member
MESSAGE_CHANNEL_RAW: %1 of the channel of the message
MESSAGE_GUILD_RAW: %1 of the server of the message

RES_VALID_MEMBER: You must specify a valid member!

RES_SET_MEMBER_NICKNAME_NEW_NAME: You must specify a valid new nickname for the member!

RES_SEND_WAIT_REPLY_VALUE_PARENT: This block can only be used in a "Wait for an answer" bl!

LEAVING_GUILD_RAW: %1 of the server of the leaving member
ON_MEMBER_LEAVE: When a member leaves a server
RES_MUST_BE_IN_ON_MEMBER_LEAVE: This block may only be used in a "When a member leaves a server" event
GET_MESSAGE: Get message with ID equal to %1 in channel %2
RES_GET_MESSAGE_CHANNEL: You must specify a valid channel on which the message is!
RES_GET_MESSAGE_VALUE: You must specify a valid message ID!
CREATE_CHANNEL: Create channel with name %1 on server %2 of type %3
